01:06:19.184 --> 01:06:22.844
The problem is that there are many lysines

1104
01:06:23.244 --> 01:06:25.544
and cysteines within an antibody structure.

1105
01:06:26.724 --> 01:06:30.274
This limits our ability to control not only the number of

1106
01:06:30.324 --> 01:06:34.124
drugs attached, but the site to which they are attached.

1107
01:06:35.944 --> 01:06:39.794
In response to this, we are experiencing a shift in the

1108
01:06:39.864 --> 01:06:40.404
industry.

1109
01:06:41.384 --> 01:06:44.864
Companies are pursuing next-generation conjugation chemistries

1110
01:06:45.404 --> 01:06:47.444
that afford us more control.

1111
01:06:48.444 --> 01:06:50.864
Some are pursuing enzymatic approaches,

1112
01:06:51.704 --> 01:06:53.724
transglutaminase, catenase.

1113
01:06:54.784 --> 01:06:57.254
Others have taken the approach of glycan remodeling,

1114
01:06:58.664 --> 01:07:01.864
reconfiguring the sugar group so that they can attach to it,

1115
01:07:02.384 --> 01:07:03.784
